# Title: A Rule Has Been Deleted From The Windows Firewall Exception List
# Author: frack113
# Date: 2022-02-19
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects when a single rules or all of the rules have been deleted from the Windows Defender Firewall
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1686.003
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/builtin/firewall_as/win_firewall_as_delete_rule.yml

EventID IN (2006, 2052) NOT (ModifyingApplication="" OR ModifyingApplication IN ("C:\\Program Files (x86)\\*", "C:\\Program Files\\*", "C:\\Windows\\WinSxS\\*") OR NOT ModifyingApplication=* OR ModifyingApplication="C:\\Windows\\System32\\svchost.exe") NOT (ModifyingApplication="*\\MsMpEng.exe" ModifyingApplication="C:\\ProgramData\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Platform\\*")